# Title capitalization rules for Mangrove documentation

All titles and headings in the Mangrove documentation follow **sentence case capitalization**:

## Core rules

- **Capitalize only the first word** of titles and headings
- **Capitalize proper nouns** (names, places, technologies, brands)
- **Use lowercase for all other words**

## Applies to

- Main page headlines (H1: `# My headline`)
- Section headings (H2, H3, H4, etc.: `## My section heading`)
- Meta title attributes in MDX files (`title="Getting started/My guide"`)
- Navigation titles in Storybook

## Examples

### ✅ Correct format
- `# Getting started with mangrove`
- `## Component structure and standards`
- `### CSS and JS references`
- `title="Getting started/React integration"`
- `# TypeScript demo component`
- `## Working with non-TypeScript code`

### ❌ Incorrect format
- `# Getting Started With Mangrove`
- `## Component Structure And Standards`
- `### CSS And JS References`
- `title="Getting Started/React Integration"`
- `# TypeScript Demo Component`
- `## Working With Non-TypeScript Code`

## Proper nouns (keep capitalized)

### Technology names
- React, TypeScript, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, Sass, SCSS
- Node.js, npm, yarn, Jest, Webpack, Vite

### Framework/library names
- Storybook, Jest, UNDRR, Mangrove
- Next.js, Vue.js, Angular

### Acronyms
- API, URL, RTL, LTR, WCAG, MDX, JSON, XML
- UI, UX, DOM, CDN, SPA

### Brand names
- GitHub, GitLab, Google Analytics, Docker
- Microsoft, Apple, Chrome, Firefox

## Correct examples with proper nouns
- `# React integration guide` ✅
- `## Working with non-TypeScript code` ✅
- `### CSS and JS references` ✅
- `# UNDRR logos` ✅
- `## GitHub workflow setup` ✅
- `### API integration patterns` ✅

## When reviewing/editing

1. Check that only the first word is capitalized
2. Verify proper nouns remain capitalized
3. Ensure Meta titles in MDX files follow the same pattern
4. Apply to both content headings and navigation structure

This approach ensures consistency across all documentation and provides a clean, readable hierarchy that matches modern documentation standards.
